post: {'type': 'pro', 'text': "Justifying a ban because it provides people with more autonomy is an inherent contradiction. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The prohibition forces users, that are otherwise law-abiding citizens, into transactions with more serious law-breakers, opening them up for the possibility to escalate to more serious crimes.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug prohibition consumes a considerable portion of public spending.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalizing drugs would increase the probability of violence and offenses.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drugs can give individuals false perceptions of reality, inducing potentially negative behaviour.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It doesn't mean that we should endanger people and harm them in order for them to not feel safe. So all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If drugs other than alcohol were legalized, alcohol sales would plummet, and a lot of jobs in the alcohol industry would disappear.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Heroin and other opiates cause [negligible](https://rationalwiki.org/wiki/Heroin#Health_effects) direct physical harm to the body. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is a tautological argument, presupposing that prohibiting drugs is morally right.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Currently, in many countries, stores which sell age-restricted products such as alcohol have strict regulations in place to ensure the consumer is of appropriate age. The same could be done with other drugs. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The criminalization of drug use is the major agitator of the economic rifts caused by drug use: illegal drug use leads to arrests which lead to arrest records and the socially imposed inability to self-produce wealth.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the long run, the standing of the U.S. government did not suffer from ending the Alcohol Prohibition in the 1930s. Any potential reputational damage from ending marijuana or other prohibitions would be fleeting.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Research suggests that [two-thirds](https://www.verywell.com/domestic-abuse-and-alcohol-62643) of incidents of domestic violence happen while the perpetrator is under the influence of alcohol.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Constitutions can be amended by the Federal Government to suit their policies.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'According to [Human Right Watch](https://www.hrw.org/news/2013/06/04/americas-decriminalize-personal-use-drugs), subjecting people to disproportionate criminal sanctions for the personal use of drugs "infringes on their autonomy".'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Various currently illegal drugs have valuable medical properties; these substances may have the potential to solve problems in our society such as mental health issues. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If the war on drugs were won, these jobs would also be lost.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Incarceration does not treat addiction; the money spent on incarcerated non-violent drug offenders could be instead used to fund addiction treatment.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Tobacco companies are investing in and moving to different technologies \\(vaping\\) as the population becomes more aware of the harms and less prone to tobacco smoking. They can tell tobacco smoking is ultimately a â€˜sinking ship' for their profits."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In 2018, the consumption patterns of most US citizens who used illicit drugs were [unproblematic](https://filtermag.org/2018/09/25/the-invisible-majority-people-whose-drug-use-is-not-problematic/). I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If drugs were legalised, all the ways it could harm other people could be criminalised, such as taking them before controlling dangerous machinery or smoking in public. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It's important to have a standardized quantity of an active substance of controlled quality to prevent overdosing unwanted effects. I think all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Information about the content of legalized drugs would be easier to find and accurate which would help people make informed and safer choice.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'A more substantial part of society will be exposed to the harmful and dangerous side effects of drugs.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The banning of alcohol [significantly increased the ability of organized crime to make money](http://prohibition.themobmuseum.org/the-history/the-rise-of-organized-crime/the-mob-during-prohibition/). That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This argument is prematurely claiming that the means \\(the legislation of drugs\\) is immoral. Whether it is moral or immoral should be decided after it has already happened and we can measure the impact on our society.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The fact that legalising drugs would not "end all crime" does not means that it would not damage criminal organizations. It\'s a step in the right direction to reduce their power.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Making things safer is always preferable.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The [war on drugs](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War_on_drugs) in the US was intended to be used as a tool to criminalise certain ethnic groups.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "A parent's drugs addiction can cause a child to suffer emotional harm and a lack of future stability as it can reduce the parent's life expectancy, causing them to die young. So drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "In the US, incarceration reduces former inmates' earnings by [40 percent](https://www.pewtrusts.org/en/research-and-analysis/reports/0001/01/01/collateral-costs) on average and limits their future economic mobility."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This ignores proportionality \\(meaning how many people were negatively affected and to what magnitude\\).'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Without producing all drugs locally inside that border and banning imports, the situation would continue to support foreign criminal activity, including associated acts of violence and social destabilisation in other places where drugs are produced but not legal. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Cheap [substitutes](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Desomorphine#Toxicity_of_%22krokodil%22) like krokodil cause severe health problems. If drugs were legal and cheaper, substitutes lose popularity.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Constitutions can be amended by the Federal Government to suit their policies.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The black market businesses won't be able to invest in productivity-increasing \\(especially immovable\\) capital, as the threat of being caught discourages such investments. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalisation of drugs could lead to better education on how to be safe around them. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization of drugs will make people aware of their consequences \\(having a prospectus like medicine with known pros and cons - like marijuana for medical usage\\). So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "The syntheses for many illicit, addictive and recreational drugs is already known, there would be high amounts of money spent on R&D for new less addictive drugs. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Cocaine is [highly addictive](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cocaine_dependence) and easy to become dependent on. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This is an argument against incarceration for drug related crimes, not for the outright legalisation of drugs. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Historically, the US government has released inaccurate or untruthful information about drugs in an attempt to stop the public from using them. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalization runs the danger of increased drug use that could impair people from doing jobs safely, making work places more dangerous.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Psychedelics are often used for [one-off, recreational and spiritual](https://www.livescience.com/61902-psychedelic-drugs-change-personality.html) experiences. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Under the influence of drugs, users are more likely to commit immoral acts.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The criminalization of drug use is the major agitator of the economic rifts caused by drug use: illegal drug use leads to arrests which lead to arrest records and the socially imposed inability to self-produce wealth.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "The ability to alter another person's mind state has potential for abuse, and utter manipulation. As a result, people will be more able to infringe on the bodily freedom/autonomy of others."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If this was true, cartels would already be moving over to newer, patented pharmaceuticals, whose costs of production is dwarfed by market price already.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Since everything is legal, users can instead choose the drugs with the most benefits and the least harms.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Kids should learn right from wrong from their parents and communities/churches. What is lawful isn't always right \\(for example: adultery\\). I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If the primary goal is defeating drug dealing and cartels, the most effective way would be just ceasing drug use by everyone. With the "added bonus" that without drug use people will also be healthier and richer. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There are often structurally similar legal compounds which can be researched instead of the illegal variation. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Further studies on the "Rat Park" experiment discussed in the video [have found](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rat_Park#Reaction_to_the_experiment) social isolation is not necessary for addiction.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In Holland, [a channel](https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCvRQKXtIGcK1yEnQ4Te8hWQ) exists just to raise awareness of drugs. It explains how and when to take them, and what to do when a friend is having an OD.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Rational discussion of the costs and benefits of smoking tobacco and negative ads led a lot of people to decide it isn't worth doing. All without prohibiting it."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Right now \\(2019\\) children [as young as eight](https://www.channel5.com/show/8-years-old-and-smuggling-drugs/) are involved in the drug trade. This would not be allowed in a regulated market. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalizing something means including it the current system of business oversight and regulation as other legal activities. This means documenting purchases and monetary transactions, as well as filing and paying taxes. This means more control over where drugs come from and money goes, rather than would be the case under prohibition or decriminalization.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Optimal treatment of addiction sometimes means [needing to taper off](https://www.therecoveryvillage.com/heroin-addiction/heroin-taper/) a drug, however, under prohibition quitting "cold turkey" is the only legal option. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legal drugs would not be the only option; there may still be a market of illegal drugs, for example if it is cheaper than the legal choice.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'A [Constitutional Amendment](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eighteenth_Amendment_to_the_United_States_Constitution) had to be voted on for the prohibition of alcohol. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Just because there are other systematic racial issues does not mean we cannot challenge this particular racist law.'}
